description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applications are invited for the post of Locum Consultant in Diabetes and General Medicine (10PA) for a 12 month fixed term contract. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The specialty of Endocrinology, Diabetes and Metabolism provides care at Queen Elizabeth, Heartlands, Good Hope and Solihull Hospitals, as well as in the community across Birmingham and Solihull.&lt;/span&gt;This post will be predominantly based at Queen Elizabeth Hospital.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join one of the largest Diabetes and Endocrinology Departments in the country providing specialist secondary, tertiary and community care. The Department has an excellent track record in clinical service, research, teaching and training. The post will support the specialist inpatient Diabetes service and provide specialist outpatient Diabetes clinics, as well as covering a share of inpatient general medicine work. The post holder will be expected to have specialty training and relevant experience in Diabetes and General Internal Medicine. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should be on the GMC specialist register or be eligible for inclusion on the register within six months of the interview date and have MRCP or equivalent.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For informal discussions, please contact Helena Gleeson (Clinical service Lead) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Helena.gleeson@uhb.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
